FBIS4-15046 "drsov066_a_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-066 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS UN Status Denied for Russians in Georgia, Tajikistan UN Status Denied for Russians in Georgia, Tajikistan PM0604090394 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 6 Apr 94 p 6 PM0604090394 Moscow PRAVDA Russian BFN [Report from roundup of news agency reports] [Text] UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali has rejected the Russian proposal to grant the status of UN forces to the Russian Army subunits deployed in Georgia and Tajikistan. Speaking in Moscow after talks with President Yeltsin, Butrus-Ghali said that the UN peacekeeping operations should be carried out by multinational forces under direct UN control.
